UYO – Wife of Governor Udom Emmanuel’s preferred successor, Mrs Patience Umo Eno has come public to declare her husband “A Golden Boy”. The gold-skinned Commissioner for Lands and Water Resources, Mr Umo Eno had since presention to the public by Governor Udom Emmanuel as his preferred successor been declared unsuitable by a section of the public to occupy the number one public office in the state for being an “albino”. Some have gone as far as gathering pictures of albinos across ages and gender on social media platforms, presenting them as soon to be leaders of the state.. Security Beefed At APC Secretariat After National Convention… Ebonyi Assembly Declares Deputy Speaker’s Seat Vacant,… In a video clip which circulated online on Sunday,  the expectant first lady,  during a consultation worship with All Nations Christian Church in Eket on Sunday said “My husband is very special and unique. They call him albino but I say he’s my golden boy. Let me tell you something, my husband’s color especially his hair color is what some ladies are paying to have”. Many have given various shades of interpretations to Mrs Eno’s public outburst. While some thought it was too early to show off herself, others have applauded her for demonstrating such “home front” support for her husband. Whatever the case may have been, “My Golden Boy” is currently trending on various social media platforms.